# MCP Tools

## Adding Tools
- Use `@mcp.tool()` with `async def`; tool docstring becomes the tool description
- Keep parameters simple: `str`, `bool`, `int`; avoid complex types
- Return `str`; Cursor consumes tool output as text

## Contract Tests
- Add tests in `tests/contracts/test_mcp_server.py`
- Verify tool exists via `server._tool_manager.list_tools()`
- Test tool behavior by calling `server._tool_manager.call_tool(name, args)`
- Mock `ContextAssembler`, `create_llm_client`, etc.; never hit real APIs

## Schema Stability
- Avoid breaking changes to tool names or parameter types
- Add optional parameters with defaults for backward compatibility
